  "body": "- Remove `NoSnap` from all charts demos using it in order to prevent regressions of untested code.\r\n- Migrate `ChartsUsageDemo` from JS to TSX\r\n- `ChartsUsageDemo` data now accepts `displayName` to change the displayed label name\r\n\r\nI couldn't properly type the `props` returned in the callbacks from `ChartsUsageDemo`. They get the \"keys\", but not the correct type for the props.\r\n\r\nEg: \r\n\r\n```tsx\r\nconst data = [\r\n  { propName: 'name', knob: 'input', defaultValue: 'John' },\r\n  { propName: 'age', knob: 'number', defaultValue: 25 },\r\n] as const;\r\n\r\n// should have\r\n\r\n// ...\r\nrenderDemo={(props) => {}}\r\n\r\n// props should be of type\r\ntype Result = {name: string; age: number}\r\n\r\n// but actually is\r\ntype Result = {name: any; age: any}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI tried many ways to fix it, but I couldn't make react specifically understand it 😢",
  "created_at": "2025-02-21T14:10:09Z",
  "updated_at": "2025-02-24T18:56:13Z",
  "closed_at": "2025-02-24T18:56:10Z",
